FBIS3-55841 "drsov008_a_94031" FBIS-SOV-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Federation Provides Georgia Long-Term Credit LD1101185394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1546 GMT 11 Jan 94 LD1101185394 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tengiz Djibuti] [Text] Moscow, January 11 (TASS) -- A long-term credit of 10 billion rubles (about 8 million U.S. dollars) has been allocated by Russia to Georgia for 1994 to help survive its depressed economy, an official from the Georgian Embassy in Moscow told ITAR-TASS on Tuesday [11 January]. Moreover, as the republic has joined the Commonwealth of Independent States, additional technical credits for keeping functioning the Georgian metallurgic and mining industries are being considered, he said. The same source reported that an agreement has been reached to plug in the Georgian power network to the united energy system of the southern Russia.
